items.description:
• @detoursf @sfgaymers
  • Meet fellow local LGBTQIA+ gamers, hosted by SF Gaymers. Join us for a night of classic arcade games and tabletop games. We also have a 20' x 10' dedicated screen to play Nintendo Switch on. Feel free to bring your own board games or your own Switch with your favorite games installed. If you have any suggestions for activities in the future, please suggest them to the host, and we will do our best to add them to the fun!
  • https://www.detoursf.com/event/every-first-saturday-gay-gaymers-social/
  • https://www.instagram.com/sfgaymers/p/C5SidvVOjSv/
items.location: The Detour, 2200A Market St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

The hottest Sunday party in the city, JOCK is packed every week with hot, sweaty, athletic boys  and girls  JOCK is ALL-STAR!

items.summary: How Weird Street Faire - Autumn Equinox 2024
items.description:
The longest-running dance festival / street parade on the West Coast returns on Saturday, September 21.

This year's theme Autumn Equinox will feature an unforgettable day of music, art, costumes, and dancing, centered at Howard and 2nd Streets in downtown San Francisco, CA.

Noon-8 p.m. All Ages. Wheelchair Accessible. Children 5 and under do not need tickets but must be accompanied by a paying adult.

 9 stages of music
 Art Alley, showcasing extreme creativity
 How Weird Marketplace, featuring unique goods
 An eclectic menu of food and drink offerings from food trucks and local restaurants
 Weirdness!

Stages:
TBA!

On Saturday September 21st, the streets of downtown San Francisco will once again be filled with colorful costumes and dancing. How Weird Street Faires stages will feature world-class electronic music, played on some of the worlds best sound systems. Cutting-edge headliners from across the Bay Area and the world will provide an unforgettable dance experience. 

Art Alley will showcase the visual arts, with live and exhibited artwork, interactive pieces, and artists selling their works. Patrons can stroll the legendary open air gallery, and be inspired by the abundance of creativity in an expanded space. Apply to sell your art at the Faire, at www.howweird.org. Spots are limited.

How Weird Marketplace will be filled with vendors from around the world selling unique goods. From clothing to art, jewelry, and accessories, Marketplace offers a unique shopping experience. Apply to vend at the Faire, at www.howweird.org. Spots are limited.
Food trucks and local restaurants will provide a wide variety of food and drinks for sale.

A world-renowned experience, How Weird Street Faire has been named one of the 10 Best Cultural Festivals in America by USA Today in 2019, and awarded SF Weeklys Best of SF Award for street fair that continues to improve and blow our minds in 2018. S.F. Chronicle has declared: How Weird festival celebrates everything that makes SF special.

Located in downtown San Francisco, How Weird draws lovers of music, art, culture, and weirdness. Our event welcomes all ages, and is wheelchair accessible. Only service dogs can enter the Faire. Glass bottles and weapons are not allowed, and bags may be searched when entering. For more information please visit: https://howweird.org/f-a-q/

The Faire is easily accessible by BART, and a short walk from the Caltrain Station and many MUNI lines. We strongly encourage everyone to take public transportation.

How Weird Street Faire is the annual benefit for the educational nonprofit, World Peace Through Technology (https://wptt.org/). WPTTs primary education project is the Immersive Learning Center (ILC), which provides STEAM educational opportunities to one of the least-served communities in California for free, six days a week. How Weird also supports other nonprofits and local charities. In the past year, donations have gone to the Haight Ashbury Food Project, Art of Peace Project, United Playaz, ARC San Francisco, ARC Solano, Sunset Youth Services, and others.

items.description:
The Haight Ashbury Street Fair is a celebration of community, culture, and creativity, featuring live music, artisanal vendors, food stalls, and family-friendly activities. Darren Nelsons poster prints will be available for purchase, with proceeds supporting the ongoing efforts of the Haight Ashbury Street Fair organization.

Press Release: Haight-Ashbury Street Fair Celebrates 45th Anniversary with Stellar Lineup
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
Haight-Ashbury Street Fair
San Francisco, CA - [July 16, 2024]
The iconic Haight-Ashbury Street Fair (HASF) is set to celebrate its 45th anniversary on Sunday, September 15, 2024. This year's event promises an unforgettable experience with an outstanding lineup of artists performing on the Stanyan and Masonic stages. Locations and set times will be published on the Haight-Ashbury Street Fair's website and social media channels shortly.
2024 Lineup Highlights:
MOONALICE: A fusion of rock and psychedelia.
Frightwig: Pioneers of the punk rock scene.
Keystone Revisited featuring Tony Saunders and Scott Guberman with special guest Narada Michael Walden.
Eric McFadden's Sgt Splendor: A mix of rock, funk, and blues, featuring Kate Vagas.
Bryan Kehoe's Los Cincos Borrachos: High-energy rockabilly tunes.
The Infamous Stiffs: Punk rock energy and attitude.
Veil's: Atmospheric and emotive alternative rock.
Milk For The Angry: Powerful and dynamic rock performance.
Matt Jaffe: Infectious pop-rock melodies.
Jethro Jeremiah: Soulful and captivating singer-songwriter.
The Young Barons: Surf rock with youthful exuberance.
The Voodoo Cabaret: Theatrical and eclectic performance.
2 TBA Youth Bands: Winners of the Battle of the Bands, in partnership with Rock Project SF.
This celebration of music, community, and culture is a testament to the enduring spirit of the Haight-Ashbury neighborhood. In addition to the musical performances, the fair will feature a diverse array of merchant and food vendor stalls, offering unique products and delicious treats.
Sponsorship Opportunities and Vendor Applications
There are still sponsorship opportunities available, as well as merchant and food vendor applications. Interested parties are encouraged to visit the Haight-Ashbury Street Fair's website for more information and to apply. As a non-profit, volunteer-run event, the fair relies on donations and community support to bring this vibrant festival to life.
Don't miss out on this historic celebration! Stay tuned for updates on set times and locations by following the Haight-Ashbury Street Fair on their website and social media channels:
Facebook
Instagram
For media inquiries, please contact: Haight-Ashbury Street Fair
kzanotto@stardustguild.co

items.summary: Oakland Pride: We Run This - Pride Block Party
items.description:
WE RUN THIS!  A Community-Powered PRIDE Block Party!

@oaklash and @nectarsocialclub are back and bigger than ever! Were here to celebrate usloud, proud, and unapologetically queer. 

Join us for our second annual We Run This!  where were creating a safer, joyful space for everyone to express their truest, queerest selves. This year, were also celebrating @nectarsocialclubs first anniversary!  A year full of incredible memories, new friendships, and unstoppable community love.

We Run This is more than just a celebration; its a fundraiser to uplift @oaklash2024 and Oaklands phenomenal queer talent and artists. Supporting our homegrown queer arts organizations is vital to keeping our community vibrant, active, and thriving. Proceeds from this event directly go to supporting your community! 

We have so much more to share with you about this years eventstay tuned! 

A huge thank you to our amazing supporters @thisisbabas.house and @centralarterydistrict for helping make this possible.

Flyer and graphics by: @shotbyguerrilla
